Definition: a percussion instrument that is made from a dried cactus branch that is hollowed out and filled with small pebbles and capped at both ends
Example: makes the sound of falling rain when tilted; origin was in Chile where tribesmen used it in ceremonies to bring rain
Synonyms: percussion_instrument, a, percussion, instrument, that, is, made, from, dried, cactus, branch, hollowed, out, and, filled, with, small, pebbles, capped, at, both, ends, makes, the, sound, of, falling, rain, when, tilted, origin, was, in, Chile, where, tribesmen, used, it, ceremonies, to, bring
Category: noun.artifact
